<p><a name="Resolution" id="Resolution"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=ATSC_Standards&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Resolution">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Resolution</span></h2>
<p>The ATSC system supports a number of different display resolutions, <a href="/wiki/Aspect_ratio" title="Aspect ratio">aspect ratios</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Frame_rate" title="Frame rate">frame rates</a>. The formats are listed here by resolution, form of scanning (<a href="/wiki/Progressive_scan" title="Progressive scan">progressive</a> or <a href="/wiki/Interlacing" title="Interlacing" class="mw-redirect">interlaced</a>), and number of frames (or fields) per second (see also the TV resolution overview at the end of this article). The table includes formats from both A/53 Part 4 (MPEG-2 Video System Characteristics) and A/63 (Standard for Coding 25/50 Hz Video).</p>
<table class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;">
<tr style="background:#eee;">
